Preconditions:
The arrays `source` and `target` must not be null.
The arrays `source` and `target` must have the same length.
The array `allowedSwaps` must not be null.
The array `allowedSwaps` must have dimensions Nx2, where N is the number of swap operations allowed.
The elements in `allowedSwaps` must be valid indices within the `source` array.

Postconditions:
The method returns an integer value representing the minimum Hamming distance between `source` and `target` after performing any amount of swap operations.
The original arrays `source` and `target` remain unchanged after the method execution.